The Biden-Harris Administration is focused on attracting global talent to strengthen the US economy and technological competitiveness. They believe that the ability to attract international talent in STEM fields has led to innovation, job creation, and new opportunities for Americans. The Departments of State and Homeland Security are announcing new actions to provide clarity and predictability for international STEM scholars, students, researchers, and experts to contribute to innovation and job creation in the United States. These actions align with the administration's efforts to remove barriers to legal immigration and promote educational exchange.